      "readmeSignals": {
        "title": "Stage 1: external system narrows to candidate ids.",
        "summary": "A 10 million document corpus takes 31 GB of RAM as float32. turbovec fits it in 4 GB - and searches it faster than FAISS. turbovec is a Rust vector index with Python bindings, built on Google Research's https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.19874 algorithm — a data-oblivious quantizer that matches the Shannon lower bound on distortion, with no codebook training and no separate train phase. Online ingest. Add vectors, they're indexed — no train step, no parameter tuning, no rebuilds as the corpus grows. Faster than FAISS. Hand-written NEON ARM and AVX-512BW x86 kernels beat FAISS IndexPQFastScan by 12–20% on ARM and match-or-beat it on x86. Filter at search time. Pass an id allowlist or a slot bitmask t",
